				<td colspan="2"><span>Okies, just wondering how exaclty the epic works...
<br />

<br />
It adds a 1.8 mod to sings, and counts as every instrument....
<br />

<br />
Lets say I get singing mastery 3, that adds .6 more mod to singing, and to any song that I sing w/o any instrument.
<br />

<br />
Now lets say I get IM3, and add .6 mod to instrument songs.
<br />

<br />
When I use epic, and a &quot;singing&quot; song, like Psalm of Veeshan, does IM or SM get used? I assume SM for that one.
<br />

<br />
Now lets say I sing wind of marr...does the epic count as a 1.8 mod to singing, or to stringed?  Since there isnt any way to tell if it is a 1.8 to all instrument, or a instrument that removes the &quot;requires: instrument type&quot; from songs like OOS, and adds 1.8 to singing.  
<br />

<br />
As far as I know, getting SM adds to songs that require singing, and all others w/o epic.  IM adds to all songs that require an instrument with an instrument OR epic.
<br />

<br />
Just making sure this is right.  Anyone know for sure?  As I am a grouping bard, I will use my epic 99% of the time for song boosts.  If singing mastery works with the epic on all songs, I would get that first, if instrument mastery works on them, then thats first on my list. Thanks.</span></td>
