				<td colspan="2"><span>Epic is 1.8 to all instrument types and singing.  IM3 and SM3
<br />
would each be .6 added modifer.
<br />

<br />
Song of Veeshan is a singing based song, so SM would be the
<br />
modifer it used.
<br />

<br />
Wind of Marr is String based, so string based mod from epic
<br />
plus IM would be used.
<br />

<br />
SM only modifies singing based songs.  Just because you don't
<br />
have an instrument in your hands doesn't mean it switches
<br />
over to a singing skill.  It still uses instrument skill it's based
<br />
off of.
<br />

<br />

<br />
You would have to get both AA types to cover all songs. Both
<br />
IM and SM.  IM being the more useful since it covers a wider
<br />
range of songs.
<br />

<br />
Recapping.  SM is only for singing skill based songs not
<br />
instrument based songs.  IM is for instrument based songs.
<br />
SM and IM both are added on to existing modifiers such as 
<br />
having your epic/instrument equipt or weather you are empty
<br />
like on a corpse run.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
